The President and Vice President recently met with 13 Asian American, Native Hawaiian, and Pacific Islander leaders to discuss various issues, including anti-Asian hate crimes, economic opportunities, equity, voting rights, and immigration reform. They promised to listen to and address the needs of these communities and expressed support for a pathway to citizenship for Dreamers, farm workers, TPS holders, and essential workers. The leaders also discussed the importance of civic engagement and vowed to protect voting rights and strengthen democracy.